-- PGE May Buy 83% Stake in Energa for Cash, Dziennik Gazeta Prawna Reports
-- Monika Rozlal
-- 2010-06-14T05:22:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-14/pge-may-buy-83-stake-in-energa-for-cash-dziennik-gazeta-prawna-reports.html

          
          
             PGE SA , Poland’s biggest power
group, may finance purchasing an 83 percent stake in Energa SA
from its own funds,  Dziennik Gazeta Prawna  reported, citing
Chief Executive Officer  Tomasz Zadroga .  
 Zadroga added that the company may also consider partly
financing with a banking loan or bond sale if it is
“favorable,” the newspaper said. PGE is one of five bidders
picked for Energa shortlist. The stake price may be between 6
billion zloty ($1.78 billion) and 8 billion zloty, the newspaper
reported.  
